# API Slice Rules

- Endpoints are thin gateways only — no business logic, DB queries, or mapping in `{Entity}Endpoints.cs`.
- Implement `IEndpoint` with `MapEndpoint(IEndpointRouteBuilder app)`. Register via assembly scan (`MapAllEndpoints()`), not manual `Program.cs` edits.
- Use **named delegate methods** for route handlers. No inline lambdas inside `MapEndpoint`.
- Map handler `Result<T>` to HTTP status codes and RFC 7807 Problem Details via `.ToProblemDetails()`.
- Each entity slice needs at least 6 endpoints: list/search (GET), get-by-id (GET), export (GET), create (POST), update (PUT), soft-delete (DELETE).
- Delete handlers set `IsDeleted = true` and save — never physical delete.
